Raw dev notes -- Google Recorder CLI: Downloading Audio with Speaker Diarization (Feb 2026)

Quick project: built a CLI tool to download recordings from Google Recorder web app.
Uses commander.js, handles auth via saved browser cookies, downloads audio files,
and extracts speaker diarization data.

Built it because Google Recorder has no export API and I needed to batch-download
recordings for transcription. The web app only lets you download one at a time.

Added an accessibility snapshot tool for debugging the DOM structure.
Chrome DevTools MCP integration for development.

Short project but useful. The a11y snapshot approach was interesting --
instead of parsing HTML, query the accessibility tree for structured content.
